# 🧩 Pull Request Template

Thank you for contributing to a MachCore project! 🎮  
Please complete the sections below to help us review your pull request efficiently.

---

## 📋 Summary

**Describe what this pull request does and why it’s needed.**  
_Example: Adds a new animation utility for display entities._

---

## 🔍 Related Issues

Link any related issues using keywords like `Fixes #123` or `Closes #456`.

---

## 🧱 Type of Change

Select all that apply:

- [ ] 🐛 Bug fix  
- [ ] ✨ New feature  
- [ ] 🧰 Code improvement / refactor  
- [ ] 📖 Documentation update  
- [ ] ⚙️ Build / configuration change  
- [ ] 🚀 Performance improvement  
- [ ] 🔒 Security fix  

---

## 🧪 Testing

**Describe how you tested your changes.**  
_Example: Verified behavior in-game on Paper 1.22.6, confirmed no console errors._

---

## ⚙️ Branch & Merge Details

- **Source branch:** (e.g., `feature/your-feature`, `hotfix/fix-issue`)  
- **Target branch:** (e.g., `develop`, `main`)  
- Ensure your branch is **up to date** with the target branch before requesting a merge.
- If this PR depends on other work, mention it here.

---

## 💬 Reviewer Notes

**Anything reviewers should know before merging?**  
_Example: Requires `core-utils` module update or configuration file change._

---

## ✅ Checklist

Please confirm the following before submission:

- [ ] My code builds and runs without errors.  
- [ ] I’ve reviewed my changes for clarity and consistency.  
- [ ] I’ve updated or added documentation/comments where necessary.  
- [ ] I’ve tested my changes in-game or with relevant systems.  
- [ ] This PR follows the [Contributor Workflow](../docs/CONTRIBUTOR_WORKFLOW.md) or [Developer Workflow](../docs/DEVELOPER_WORKFLOW.md).  
- [ ] All conversations and checks will be resolved before merging.  

---

### ⚙️ Notes for Maintainers

Pull requests into:
- `develop` should originate from **feature/** branches.  
- `main` should originate from **develop** or **hotfix/** branches.

---

**Thank you for helping build better tools and experiences with MachCore! ⚙️**